"{\"abstract\":\"Pinyin-to-character (P2C) conversion is the core component of pinyin-based Chinese input method engine (IME). However, the conversion is seriously compromised by the ambiguities of Chinese characters corresponding to pinyin as well as the predefined fixed vocabularies. To alleviate such inconveniences, we propose a neural P2C conversion model augmented by an online updated vocabulary with a sampling mechanism to support open vocabulary learning during IME working. Our experiments show that the proposed method outperforms commercial IMEs and state-of-the-art traditional models on standard corpus and true inputting history dataset in terms of multiple metrics and thus the online updated vocabulary indeed helps our IME effectively follows user inputting behavior.\",\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"3322871\",\"name\":\"Zhuosheng Zhang\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/3322871\"},{\"authorId\":\"2572506\",\"name\":\"Yafang Huang\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/2572506\"},{\"authorId\":\"153716230\",\"name\":\"Hai Zhao\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/153716230\"}],\"citationVelocity\":0,\"citations\":[{\"arxivId\":\"1909.01063\",\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":null,\"name\":\"Zhuosheng Zhang\"},{\"authorId\":\"143744667\",\"name\":\"Zhen Meng\"},{\"authorId\":\"47941144\",\"name\":\"Hai Zhao\"}],\"doi\":null,\"intent\":[\"methodology\"],\"isInfluential\":false,\"paperId\":\"ea4d58cfc52b98c363ad70d0507ca1184795f621\",\"title\":\"A Smart Sliding Chinese Pinyin Input Method Editor on Touchscreen\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/ea4d58cfc52b98c363ad70d0507ca1184795f621\",\"venue\":\"ArXiv\",\"year\":2019},{\"arxivId\":\"1809.02794\",\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"3322871\",\"name\":\"Zhuosheng Zhang\"},{\"authorId\":\"150352923\",\"name\":\"Yuwei Wu\"},{\"authorId\":\"30658665\",\"name\":\"Z. Li\"},{\"authorId\":\"47941144\",\"name\":\"Hai Zhao\"}],\"doi\":null,\"intent\":[\"backgro